<example id="example-1">
<title> Constant acceleration </title>
<para id="element-19">
<term>Problem : </term> A car moving with constant acceleration covers two successive kilometers in 20 s and 30 s respectively. Find the acceleration of the car.
</para>
<para id="element-20"><term>Solution : </term> Let "u" and "a" be the initial velocity and acceleration of the car. Applying third equation of motion for first kilometer, we have :
</para>


<para id="element-21">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
